  "prompt": "When is surge pricing on Uber generally in effect in Detroit and how high does it go?",
  "response": "Surge pricing on Uber in Detroit, as in other cities, typically occurs during peak demand times when the number of ride requests exceeds the number of available drivers. This can happen during:\n\n1. **Rush Hours:** Weekday mornings (around 7 AM to 9 AM) and evenings (around 4 PM to 7 PM).\n2. **Special Events:** Concerts, sports events, or festivals can lead to increased demand.\n3. **Weather Conditions:** Bad weather can surge demand for rides.\n4. **Late-Night Hours:** Especially on weekends, around bar closing times.\n\nThe exact multiplier for surge pricing can vary based on demand, but it often ranges from 1.5x to 3x the normal fare, and in some cases, it can go even higher under extreme conditions. For the most accurate and real-time information, it's best to check the app during your intended travel times.",
